say something! Miss Lu!

00:17:29.680 --> 00:17:30.310
Miss Lu!

00:17:30.510 --> 00:17:31.880
Miss Lu, just a few words!

00:17:31.880 --> 00:17:32.590
Miss Lu!

00:17:33.000 --> 00:17:33.480
Miss Lu, please say something!

00:17:33.480 --> 00:17:34.000
Yizhen!

00:17:34.550 --> 00:17:35.070
Yizhen!

00:17:47.880 --> 00:17:48.480
Yizhen!

00:17:49.070 --> 00:17:49.730
Move aside!

00:17:50.590 --> 00:17:51.050
Yizhen!

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:54.550
Miss Lu!

00:17:54.550 --> 00:17:55.240
Miss Lu!

00:18:45.160 --> 00:18:45.960
Where is this?

00:18:47.350 --> 00:18:47.950
My home.

00:18:49.160 --> 00:18:52.090
And you're the first young lady
to ever set foot in it.

00:18:54.110 --> 00:18:57.310
Mr. Du, I appreciate you
getting me out of that situation,

00:18:57.720 --> 00:18:59.880
but we're hardly acquainted
enough for this.

00:18:59.880 --> 00:19:00.440
So,

00:19:00.440 --> 00:19:02.240
please, just take me back to my apartment.

00:19:02.240 --> 00:19:03.170
Your apartment?

00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:06.310
Do you think your apartment would be safe

00:19:06.310 --> 00:19:08.170
if the university is under siege?

00:19:10.110 --> 00:19:12.770
Actually, this isn't the second time
we've met.

00:19:42.030 --> 00:19:43.510
The one in the plaid is me.

00:19:44.590 --> 00:19:46.240
The youngest one is Si Min.

00:19:47.920 --> 00:19:49.550
And the one in white...

00:19:50.110 --> 00:19:50.970
Guan Jingning.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.860
She's Guan Cen's younger sister.

00:19:56.880 --> 00:19:58.240
The one in light colors is Guan Cen,

00:19:58.240 --> 00:20:00.170
and the one in darker clothes is me.

00:20:00.310 --> 00:20:03.710
That year, the Longhua Temple Fair
was exceptionally grand,

00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:06.080
and the five of us
had the time of our lives.

00:20:06.550 --> 00:20:07.440
It was roughly

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:08.920
when Guan Cen and I

00:20:08.920 --> 00:20:10.580
went to watch the dragon dance

00:20:11.110 --> 00:20:13.570
that you and Jingning
got separated from us.

00:20:16.720 --> 00:20:17.720
I have no memory

00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:20.440
of you—of any of you.

00:20:20.720 --> 00:20:23.160
Since you were a friend
Si Min brought along,

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:24.690
that was our first meeting.

00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:25.480
So

00:20:26.290 --> 00:20:28.350
it makes sense
we don't appear in your memories.

00:20:28.350 --> 00:20:29.150
What else?

00:20:31.880 --> 00:20:33.610
A month after you went missing,

00:20:33.790 --> 00:20:35.240
the police found you

00:20:35.240 --> 00:20:36.510
in an abandoned factory.

00:20:36.510 --> 00:20:39.070
You were disoriented
and barely conscious.

00:20:40.000 --> 00:20:41.110
After you regained awareness,

00:20:41.110 --> 00:20:42.680
the police questioned you repeatedly,

00:20:42.680 --> 00:20:43.270
but it was

00:20:44.350 --> 00:20:45.680
as if you had completely

00:20:45.680 --> 00:20:46.830
lost the memory of that period.

00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:49.400
The doctors concluded that your mind

00:20:50.110 --> 00:20:51.510
had sealed off those memories

00:20:51.510 --> 00:20:52.970
as a way to protect itself.

00:20:58.400 --> 00:20:59.440
These are

00:20:59.510 --> 00:21:01.400
all the reports related

00:21:02.200 --> 00:21:03.590
to the incident from back then—

00:21:03.590 --> 00:21:05.390
I've kept every one I could find.

00:21:05.880 --> 00:21:06.580
[Two Suspects Detained
in Girl Kidnap Case]

00:21:06.580 --> 00:21:07.290
[The Killer Remains at Large]

00:21:18.590 --> 00:21:19.440
Lu Jialei...

00:21:20.840 --> 00:21:21.840
You are Lu Jialei.

00:21:31.760 --> 00:21:33.310
Were you planning
to hide this from me forever

00:21:33.310 --> 00:21:35.200
if this hadn't come out?

00:21:37.640 --> 00:21:39.240
I can't speak for the others,

00:21:39.480 --> 00:21:40.880
but I've always believed

00:21:41.030 --> 00:21:43.230
you have the right
to know your own past.

00:21:43.950 --> 00:21:44.950
Yizhen,

00:21:45.920 --> 00:21:47.590
please don't be angry.

00:21:48.240 --> 00:21:49.610
I used to think

00:21:49.830 --> 00:21:51.920
that keeping those memories away

00:21:51.920 --> 00:21:53.350
would spare you from pain

00:21:53.700 --> 00:21:56.100
and prevent you from being retraumatized.

00:21:56.310 --> 00:21:58.510
The truth is, your parents and I,

00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:00.690
we all want what's best for you.

00:22:02.590 --> 00:22:04.640
If there's anything you want to know now,

00:22:04.640 --> 00:22:06.700
I'll tell you everything I remember.

00:22:11.310 --> 00:22:12.310
Even though I firmly believe

00:22:12.310 --> 00:22:14.310
you have the right to know your past,

00:22:15.030 --> 00:22:15.830
I still hope

00:22:17.320 --> 00:22:19.160
you won't let it consume you.

00:22:20.160 --> 00:22:21.960
Perhaps leaving the past behind

00:22:22.110 --> 00:22:24.680
is life's way of protecting you,
don't you think?

00:22:24.680 --> 00:22:27.240
What matters is cherishing the present
and living in the now—

00:22:27.240 --> 00:22:28.720
don't you think?

00:22:35.030 --> 00:22:36.030
I'll get the door.

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:46.680
You are...

00:22:50.510 --> 00:22:51.260
Mrs. Xiang?

00:22:55.170 --> 00:22:55.830
Mrs. Xiang.

00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:57.030
My child,

00:22:57.550 --> 00:22:59.150
you've been through so much.

00:23:02.520 --> 00:23:05.250
I found this among Man's things
after she passed.

00:23:05.880 --> 00:23:07.040
I read it

00:23:07.830 --> 00:23:10.030
and felt you should be the one
to have it.

00:23:29.800 --> 00:23:31.470
She was my closest friend

00:23:32.390 --> 00:23:34.110
when I felt most alone.

00:23:35.720 --> 00:23:37.650
Whenever people looked down on me,

00:23:38.030 --> 00:23:39.640
she'd always stand up for me,

00:23:39.920 --> 00:23:40.790
and comfort me.

00:23:41.640 --> 00:23:43.440
Through my hardest times,

00:23:43.960 --> 00:23:44.980
she was there by my side.

00:23:44.980 --> 00:23:46.240
[How do we reclaim the happiness
we once knew?]

00:23:47.040 --> 00:23:49.510
[The friends who were everything,
now fading into strangers.]

00:23:49.510 --> 00:23:51.960
But when she needed me the most...

00:23:52.160 --> 00:23:54.030
I thought
she had betrayed our friendship,

00:23:54.030 --> 00:23:55.480
so I shut her out.

00:23:59.150 --> 00:24:01.900
[I don't deserve it.]

00:24:47.070 --> 00:24:47.590
Stop!

00:25:06.260 --> 00:25:08.380
[Lu Jialei, 6 years old, female]

00:25:11.870 --> 00:25:12.410
[I don't regret a thing.]

00:25:27.040 --> 00:25:29.640
[Xiang Man's Hospital Medical Records]

00:25:32.440 --> 00:25:34.090
The injury occurred

00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:37.900
one week before the incident.

00:25:44.730 --> 00:25:45.380
Hello.

00:25:47.420 --> 00:25:49.060
Hello, Miss. You're here again.

00:25:49.060 --> 00:25:50.770
Are you looking for Mr. Zhang again?

00:25:50.770 --> 00:25:53.100
Yes, could you please
ask him to come here?

00:25:54.160 --> 00:25:55.160
He's not in today.

00:25:55.770 --> 00:25:57.030
He didn't come to work?

00:25:58.070 --> 00:25:59.310
How many days has he been absent?

00:25:59.310 --> 00:26:00.310
Just a couple of days.

00:26:00.310 --> 00:26:02.240
You know his girlfriend passed away—

00:26:02.240 --> 00:26:04.440
he's just taking some time for himself.

00:26:05.550 --> 00:26:07.070
Do you know where he lives?

00:26:07.810 --> 00:26:08.440
Yes, I do.

00:26:09.070 --> 00:26:10.730
Are you planning to visit him?

00:26:11.070 --> 00:26:13.830
I'm worried something
might have happened to him too.

00:26:13.830 --> 00:26:15.030
That's a fair point.

00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:17.070
Honestly, Mr. Zhang's always

00:26:17.070 --> 00:26:18.480
been good to us.

00:26:18.750 --> 00:26:21.080
I ought to find time
to check on him as well.

00:26:21.410 --> 00:26:24.060
[Shanghai Institute of Forensic Medicine]

00:26:25.590 --> 00:26:26.240
Ding Eryi?

00:26:28.510 --> 00:26:29.590
The inspector's here.

00:26:29.590 --> 00:26:30.440
Thank you for your hard work,
Director Wang.

00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:31.770
Hello, Inspector Guan.

00:26:32.650 --> 00:26:33.510
This is for you.

00:26:36.600 --> 00:26:38.510
You only order me around like this

00:26:38.830 --> 00:26:40.610
because you know I'm too nice to say no.

00:26:40.610 --> 00:26:41.210
By the way,

00:26:41.510 --> 00:26:43.240
that suspect from your recent case—

00:26:43.240 --> 00:26:46.240
wasn't she the victim
from that Kidnap Case years ago?

00:26:46.610 --> 00:26:47.770
Her name is

00:26:49.170 --> 00:26:50.500
Lu... Lu...

00:26:51.270 --> 00:26:51.880
Lu Yizhen?

00:26:51.990 --> 00:26:52.640
Yes,

00:26:52.960 --> 00:26:54.030
that's the one!

00:26:54.550 --> 00:26:55.750
My master personally

00:26:55.750 --> 00:26:58.240
performed the autopsies
for that fire years ago.

00:26:58.240 --> 00:26:59.590
The horror of that scene

00:26:59.590 --> 00:27:01.200
is still vivid in my mind.

00:27:02.270 --> 00:27:03.110
Exactly.

00:27:03.350 --> 00:27:05.200
So why has she returned
to Shanghai now?

00:27:05.200 --> 00:27:07.060
And how did she end up as a suspect?

00:27:07.550 --> 00:27:08.680
How is she now?

00:27:10.000 --> 00:27:10.930
What do you mean?

00:27:11.510 --> 00:27:13.440
I mean, what's she like as a person?

00:27:13.550 --> 00:27:15.960
And how deeply
has that incident affected her?

00:27:15.960 --> 00:27:18.160
She's just a suspect to us
at the police station.

00:27:18.160 --> 00:27:20.160
I wouldn't know much about her personally.

00:27:20.160 --> 00:27:21.360
Enough digressions—

00:27:21.580 --> 00:27:23.110
you haven't even mentioned

00:27:23.240 --> 00:27:26.170
the new findings in the report
to Inspector Guan yet.

00:27:26.950 --> 00:27:28.350
Right, take a look at this.

00:27:28.350 --> 00:27:31.150
Please take a seat, Master.
Let me get you some tea.

00:27:39.390 --> 00:27:40.060
Sulfur?

00:27:40.550 --> 00:27:41.270
Correct.

00:27:41.420 --> 00:27:42.620
I re-examined it

00:27:42.640 --> 00:27:43.990
as you requested.

00:27:44.350 --> 00:27:46.510
While both are sodium azide,

00:27:46.620 --> 00:27:48.530
this sample contains sulfur,

00:27:48.940 --> 00:27:51.050
whereas the earlier one was
of much higher purity—

00:27:51.050 --> 00:27:53.180
the difference is quite significant.

00:27:54.100 --> 00:27:55.560
Under what circumstances

00:27:55.680 --> 00:27:57.940
would sulfur be present in sodium azide?

00:27:58.110 --> 00:27:59.720
It's hard to say definitively.

00:27:59.720 --> 00:28:02.070
Sodium azide is mostly used
as a preservative,

00:28:02.070 --> 00:28:04.000
but only for industrial purposes.

00:28:10.530 --> 00:28:11.180
Hey!

00:28:12.040 --> 00:28:14.100
He's actually walking off like that?

00:28:38.550 --> 00:28:39.160
Zhang Zhi—

00:28:41.180 --> 00:28:42.180
Zhang Zhiqiang!

00:28:58.270 --> 00:28:59.400
Something's wrong!

00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:00.720
Get up!

00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:02.030
Why are you following me?

00:29:02.030 --> 00:29:02.590
Let go!

00:29:02.960 --> 00:29:03.590
Release her!

00:29:03.590 --> 00:29:04.400
Let her go! Don't move!

00:29:04.400 --> 00:29:05.130
Stay back!

00:29:05.160 --> 00:29:05.890
Release her!

00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:07.400
Letting her go is your only way out!

00:29:07.400 --> 00:29:08.720
There's no way out for me!

00:29:08.720 --> 00:29:09.640
Let me go!

00:29:09.870 --> 00:29:10.480
Just let me go!

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:11.140
Don't move!

00:29:11.510 --> 00:29:12.440
Zhang Zhiqiang,

00:29:12.830 --> 00:29:13.560
listen to me.

00:29:13.640 --> 00:29:14.440
Shut up!

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:17.000
I-I came here to give you something.

00:29:17.020 --> 00:29:17.940
What is it?

00:29:19.350 --> 00:29:21.210
Something Xiang Man left for you.

00:29:22.110 --> 00:29:22.880
Where is it?

00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:24.520
On the ground,

00:29:24.960 --> 00:29:25.560
in the bag.

00:29:28.160 --> 00:29:29.890
It's a drawing she made for you—

00:29:30.350 --> 00:29:31.750
of your future together.

00:29:33.070 --> 00:29:35.270
She wanted to return to Suzhou with you.

00:29:35.360 --> 00:29:36.670
After graduation,

00:29:37.310 --> 00:29:38.640
she'd become a teacher,

00:29:39.720 --> 00:29:41.380
and you'd open a dye workshop.

00:29:41.550 --> 00:29:43.030
You'd have two children,

00:29:44.680 --> 00:29:46.790
and a large house

00:29:47.170 --> 00:29:48.130
by the river.

00:29:48.510 --> 00:29:49.160
You'd also...

00:29:49.160 --> 00:29:50.160
Stop! Don't say another word!